Defn (Most of the meanings are derived f: a structure that has a roof and walls and stands more or less permanently in one place. Includes houses, grandstands, booths, towers, and skyscrapers.

mapillary-public65: {Pothole, Parking, Road, Bike Lane, Service Lane, Crosswalk - Plain, Lane Marking - General, Lane Marking - Crosswalk}
Defn (Most of the meanings are derived f: a long, narrow stretch with a smoothed or paved surface, made for traveling by motor vehicle, between two or more points; street or highway. Often bounded by curbs.
a human being who is not a motorcyclist, bicyclist, or rider_other  (could be a motor vehicle passenger)
a human relying on a motorcycle/moped for movement. Must be actively riding the motorcycle/moped (not standing nearby it).

mapillary-public65: {Traffic Sign (Back), Traffic Sign (Front), Traffic Sign Frame}
Defn (Most of the meanings are derived f: a sign usually on the side of a street or highway bearing symbols or words of warning or direction to motorists or pedestrians
an upright hydrant for drawing water to use in fighting a fire
a money-operated timer located next to a parking space; depositing money into it entitles you to park your car there for a specified length of time
a long seat for more than one person
a rack for parking bicycles
large outdoor signboard
the atmosphere and outer space as viewed from the earth
a long (usually round) rod of wood or metal or plastic. includes lamp posts (excluding the light) and streetlight poles (excluding the light)

a barrier, railing, or other upright structure, typically of metal, wire, or wood, enclosing an area of ground to mark a boundary, control access, or prevent escape. It is generally less sturdy than a guardrail and can be a taller, more flimsy structure.
a barrier consisting of a horizontal bar and supports; a railing at the side of a staircase or balcony to prevent people from falling

a strong fence/railing at the side of a road or in the middle of an expressway, intended to reduce the risk of serious accidents. A guardrail sits low to the ground and is made of thick horizontal metal rails.
a lump or mass of hard consolidated mineral matter
a light, plastic disk propelled with a flip of the wrist for recreation or competition
sports equipment for skiing on snow
a board that resembles a broad ski or a small surfboard; used in a standing position to slide down snow-covered slopes
round object that is hit or thrown or kicked in games
plaything consisting of a light frame covered with tissue paper; flown in wind at end of a string. Includes kites for windsurfing.
an implement used in baseball by the batter
the handwear used by fielders in playing baseball
a board with wheels that is ridden in a standing or crouching position and propelled by foot
a narrow buoyant board for riding surf
a racket used to play tennis
an open fabric of string or rope or wire woven together at regular intervals
statue or a three-dimensional work of art
(architecture) a tall vertical cylindrical structure standing upright and used to support a structure
an ornamental structure in a pool or lake from which one or more jets of water are pumped into the air. Includes the jet of water.
a sheet of canvas or other material stretched on a frame and used to keep the sun or rain off a storefront, window, doorway, or deck. Should be attached to a building.
clothing in general, not currently being worn by a human being
long strip of cloth or paper used for decoration or advertising
emblem usually consisting of a rectangular piece of cloth of distinctive design
hanging cloth used as a blind (especially for a window). does not include shower curtains.
a curtain that keeps water from splashing out of the shower area
a cushion to support the head of a sleeping person
a thick, rectangular piece of absorbent cloth for drying or wiping

a floor covering of thick woven material or animal skin -- just with limited size, covers only a small section of the floor. Includes rugs, and floor mats (door mats, bath mat). Does not include carpet.
Trees, hedges, and all kinds of vertically growing vegetation (for example, must be higher than lawn grass)
a wheeled vehicle that has two wheels and is moved by foot pedals
This includes cars, jeeps, SUVs, vans with a continuous body shape (i.e. the driverâ€™s cabin and cargo compartment are one). Does not include trailers, which have their own separate class.
a small motor vehicle with three wheels that is used as a taxi.
a motor vehicle with two wheels and a strong frame
an aircraft that has a fixed wing and is powered by propellers or jets
a large vehicle carrying many passengers; used for public transport. Typically has swing doors, more than 4 wheels, tires larger than a regular car, and an illuminated front sign
All vehicles that move on rails, e.g. trams, trains.
an automotive vehicle suitable for hauling
a large transport conveyance designed to be pulled by a truck or tractor
any slow-moving wheeled object, such as strollers, wheelchairs, and carts

River or lake. River: a large natural stream of water, with possible rapids. Lake: a body of (usually fresh) water surrounded by land. Lakes generally have very still water. Should appear naturally formed.
A sea or ocean. Generally has large amounts of surf. Unlike a river or a lake, one generally cannot sea the far bank of a sea/ocean.

all other kinds of water, e.g. puddles, ditchwater, aquariums, shallow artificially made ponds, zoo ponds, flooded areas, bathtub water, water coming out of a fire hydrant, water from a kitchen faucet, etc. Is not a lake, river, fountain, swimming pool, or sea.
pool that provides a facility for swimming; includes jacuzzi
a steep descent of the water of a river
an architectural partition with a height and length greater than its thickness; used to divide or enclose an area or to support another structure
a framework of wood or metal that contains a glass windowpane and is built into a wall or roof to admit light or air
A blind for privacy or to keep out light. Placed indoors on a window.
